OL,7,FMr Heywood told the court: "Their
OL,8,Factions make it clear that, whichever
OL,9,Fone of them actually started the fire,
OL,10,Feach of them shared the intention to
OL,11,Fmurder all the occupants and each
OL,12,Fassisted and/or encouraged the other
OL,13,Fto carry that out as planned.
OL,15,F"As to why they went to that house on
OL,16,Fthat night, and as to why they did
OL,17,Fwhat they did, these are not matters
OL,18,Fwhich the prosecution need to prove.
OL,19,FIt may never be possible to know why.
